<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,1438,2093]" lastBlockId="2.[810,1452,1438,1502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="264">
Abdomen 
<quantity box="[327,461,1845,1871]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.76" pageId="2" pageNumber="264" unit="mm" value="0.476">0.476 mm</quantity>
long excluding genital appendages, dorsal surfaces of all abdominal segments bearing few setae. Male genital appendages (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1191,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-141@4.[151,1436,1191,1725]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Paleopsychoda jarzembowskii sp. nov., male, holotype number 1615A (D. Azar collection), genitalia. A, Microphotograph. B, Line drawing. Cox, gonocoxite; Par, paramere; Sty, gonostylus; Sur, surstylus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820896/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="264">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
) with stylus (
<quantity box="[317,437,1956,1982]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.14" pageId="2" pageNumber="264" unit="mm" value="0.214">0.214 mm</quantity>
) bearing two apical spines; a specialized long seta strongly curved in its middle part arising between coxite (
<quantity box="[403,520,2029,2056]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" pageId="2" pageNumber="264" unit="mm" value="0.205">0.205 mm</quantity>
) and stylus; parameres paired with apically series of four strong setae with incurved apices; surstyli joined basally, bearing apically two strong setae on each.
</paragraph>
